26.2 Euler-angle hypothesis: initially looked strong
Tried a simpler idea — what if each decoded value (`s8/127 * scale[c] + bias[c]`) is a standalone Euler angle in radians, with no unit-norm
constraint needed at all? Converting to degrees on the high-motion track
(`0x312b14`) gave very plausible-looking joint angles: a clean swing
between ~70–80° on one axis, ~12–30° on another, small (<5°) wobble on
the third — exactly the shape of a real arm/hand animation, with 0
